research_tastes:
  - taste_id: btc_robust_alpha_taste_v1
    title: BTC Robust Alpha Taste v1
    status: active
    task_scope:
      - btc_benchmark
    purpose: A conservative BTC research taste that prioritizes robust, causal, after-cost evidence over leaderboard-chasing dev scores.
    principles:
      - Prefer causal, low-parameter rules before model-heavy strategies.
      - Treat net-after-costs and gate behavior as more important than raw Sharpe.
      - Require next-open, funding-aware, cost-multiplier, turnover, random-percentile, and per-year context before promotion.
      - Run negative controls or robustness checks early when a result looks too strong.
      - Preserve failed directions when they reduce future search space.
    ranking_heuristics:
      - expected_information_gain
      - leakage_risk
      - implementation_cost
      - robustness_to_costs
      - transferability_to_holdout
      - evidence_diversity
    anti_patterns:
      - optimizing only one development metric
      - adding high-dimensional features before a baseline ladder exists
      - ignoring turnover or execution-mode sensitivity
      - accepting unexplained fold or year concentration
      - treating disqualified strategies as candidate wins
    public_brief: docs/reference/scientist-components.md

